You can define a setter that throws in order to throw without using &#x27;use strict;&#x27;. However, additions will still be silent :(<p><a href="https://gist.github.com/vjeux/6b390e6a6bb51e24b646" rel="nofollow">https://gist.github.com/vjeux/6b390e6a6bb51e24b646</a><p><pre><code>    __DEV__ = true;
    var array = [&#x27;a&#x27;, &#x27;b&#x27;, &#x27;c&#x27;]
    deepFreezeAndThrowOnMutationInDev(array)
    array[0] = 10;
    Error: You attempted to set the key `0` with the value `10` on an object that is meant to be immutable and has been frozen.</code></pre>
